						               													<description>Be the first player to make it from the vegetable crisper to the freezer by win four poem-writing rounds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player is the judge, who spins a spinner to select the poem category (gross, sad, mad, pretty, silly, happy, gross) The remaining players write poems, based on a subject selected from their hand of subject cards, and using magnetic word tiles selected from the word board arrange them on their play board to form their poem befitting the category and subject. At the end of the three minute timer period, the judge selects the poem that is the best match of subject and category and declares the round winner, whose playing piece moves up one space towards the freezer on the score track. The judgeship passes to the left and play continues until one player wins their fourth poem round.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
